text.tspan: This has already been partly demonstrated, using DSharp:
- WindSoC/GFESoC are standard, including the Debug Module
- The host-side can already talk to the Debug Module over OCL
- Using DSharp, we're able to use debugger commands to control the CPU
(read/write regs and mem, start/stop/step, load ELF file, ...)
We already have a C 'gdbstub' that can mediate between GDB and the Debug Module.
It just has to be incorporated within 'C Tests'.
For CPUs whose Debug Modules use the 'Program Buffer' method:
- Our current gdbstub does not support this; we'd have to extend it.
